genStub

public static java.lang.String genStub(org.eclipse.jdt.core.ICompilationUnit compilationUnit,
                                       java.lang.String destTypeName,
                                       org.eclipse.jdt.core.IMethod method,
                                       JUnitStubUtility.GenStubSettings settings,
                                       java.lang.String extraAnnotations,
                                       org.eclipse.jdt.ui.wizards.NewTypeWizardPage.ImportsManager imports)
                                throws org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException
Generates a stub. Given a template method, a stub with the same signature will be constructed so it can be added to a type.

Parameters:
compilationUnit - the compilation unit
destTypeName - The name of the type to which the method will be added to (Used for the constructor)
method - A method template (method belongs to different type than the parent)
settings - Options as defined above (GENSTUB_*)
extraAnnotations - the annotations to add
imports - Imports required by the sub are added to the imports structure
Returns:
The unformatted stub
Throws:
org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException
